nodes.bodyText:
This seems to do a lot of unneeded work if the compared objects are not equal. I think you should short-circuit the checks like this:
if (!this.getContig().equals(b.getContig())) return false;
if (this.getStart() != b.getStart()) return false;
...

It's a little less readable but IMO the efficiency costs are worth it.

